We performed statistical tests in MATLAB and R/RStudio. The assumption of normality was verified with Anderson–Darling and Shapiro–Wilks tests, and F-tests were used to verify equality of variance. Comparisons between groups were performed using two-tailed, two-sample or paired t-tests with either equal or unequal variances (based on the result from the associated F-test). In the event that the dataset failed the normality tests, nonparametric tests were utilized (Mann–Whitney–Wilcoxon test). Finally, Spearman rank nonparametric correlation tests were used to measure potential association between subjects’ reported motion sickness levels and their pretest MSSQ percentiles. A required level of significance of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
